import sys
input = sys.stdin.readline

def solution(items: list, n: int):
    min_idx = min(range(len(items)), key=items.__getitem__)
    return 'Alice' if items[min_idx] < items[0] else 'Bob'
t = int(input())
for _ in range(t):
    n = int(input())
    items = list(map(int, input().split()))
    print(solution(items, n))
